>
  <p>
    The TUI lives under <code>internal/tui</code> and is built on
    <a href="https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea">Bubble Tea</a> with
    <a href="https://github.com/charmbracelet/lipgloss">Lip Gloss</a> for styling. It is
    designed as a set of composable view models, each of which subscribes to the godex
    event bus.
  </p>

  <h2>What it shows</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Streaming assistant output, with tool calls inlined.</li>
    <li>Permission prompts for tools that need approval.</li>
    <li>Todo and goal state updated live as the agent works.</li>
    <li>An inline session picker for resume and switching.</li>
    <li>A compact command for shrinking visible context mid-session.</li>
    <li>Text selection and copy-paste flows tuned for terminals.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why view models per panel</h2>
  <p>
    Each panel — chat transcript, todo list, picker, status bar — is its own model, with
    its own subscriptions to the event bus. That means panels can be added, swapped, or
    rearranged without entangling the rest of the UI. It also means a future remote front
    end can subscribe to the same events and render however it wants.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
